*design*.md

# CLAUDE.md is kept local-only fleet-wide across alpha-engine repos
# (Brian decision, 2026-03-22 — see sibling repos alpha-engine,
# alpha-engine-research, alpha-engine-backtester): it tends to carry
# infrastructure detail (deploy sequences, service topology, instance
# config) that shouldn't be public. Untracked on purpose; never commit.
CLAUDE.md

# Config — canonical source is SSM Parameter Store at
# /alpha-engine/dashboard/{config.yaml,live-config.yaml}. boot-pull.sh
# hydrates these from SSM on every run. The local files exist only
# as a working copy on the EC2 instance; never commit them. Use the
# .example files for onboarding.
config.yaml
live/config.yaml

# Bootstrap-time secrets — canonical source is SSM SecureString at
# /alpha-engine/dashboard/secrets/*. The local files below should
# not exist post-migration (2026-05-21); kept gitignored only in
# case a local dev temporarily reconstructs them for setup testing.
live/infrastructure/certs/
live/infrastructure/secrets.env

# macOS
.DS_Store

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
venv/

# Local flow-doctor sqlite store (created by tests + local invocations of
# setup_logging() — production stores live at /tmp/flow_doctor.db on Lambda
# and are ephemeral; the local file here is just test scratch).
flow_doctor.db

# Hugo blog build output (source is tracked, built files are not)
blog/public/
blog/resources/

# Hugo blog output copied into the marketing Astro static dir at build time
# (npm run build:blog inside marketing/ runs hugo --destination here).
# CF Pages reruns this on every deploy via the prebuild step.
marketing/public/blog/
# Gitleaks config (symlink to shared config)
.gitleaks.toml

.gitleaksbaseline.json
